WEBVTT

00:11:58.551 --> 00:12:01.738
Right afterwards, somebody asked her,

00:12:01.762 --> 00:12:04.269
they interviewed her,
and she was quoted as saying,

00:12:04.293 --> 00:12:08.070
"I felt as if rage vanished
from within my heart

00:12:08.094 --> 00:12:11.852
and the blood in my veins
began to flow again."

00:12:12.173 --> 00:12:13.640
Isn't that incredible?

00:12:14.021 --> 00:12:17.916
I mean, what a picture of grace,
what a hero of grace.

00:12:17.940 --> 00:12:20.193
And there's a lesson in there
for all of us.

00:12:20.217 --> 00:12:21.948
That as theologian John Piper said,

00:12:21.972 --> 00:12:26.864
"Grace is power, not just pardon."

00:12:27.974 --> 00:12:30.228
And if you think about it,